# =====================================================================
#  CATCH-ALL HYGIENE RULES (added 2026 Jun) — keep local junk out.
#
#  WHAT BELONGS IN THE REPO (everything else is local-only / invisible):
#    - module folders  m001/ … m010/  (and new mXXX/ you intend to push)
#    - _shared/  .validation/  .github/  .githooks/
#    - the TS/Deno build files (deno.json, build_definitions.ts, etc.)
#    - DOC_*.md
#    - the two CSV backbones: population_estimates_only.csv,
#      survey_data_unified.csv
#
#  Anything matched below is LOCAL-ONLY on purpose. If you make a new file
#  that you DO want pushed and it's hidden, `git add -f <file>` to override.
# =====================================================================

# --- Backups & temp copies ---
*.bak
*.bak-*
*.orig
*~

# --- Big data / geospatial / model caches ---
*.tif
*.tiff
*.geojson
*.gpkg
*.shp
*.shx
*.dbf
*.prj
*.rds
*.nc
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.7z

# --- Documents / reports / binaries ---
*.pdf
*.xlsm
*.html
*.py

# --- Data CSVs: ONLY the two backbones are committed ---
*.csv
!population_estimates_only.csv
!survey_data_unified.csv

# --- Local notes at repo root (committed docs are DOC_*.md / README.md) ---
/*.md
!/DOC_*.md
!/README.md

# --- Local working & output folders ---
# Any NN_-numbered folder is a local pipeline/tool dir (06_, 08_, …)
[0-9][0-9]_*/
ARCHIVE/
results/
count_down/
**/cache/

# --- Nested repos that live here but push to their OWN remotes ---
# (kept out so the parent repo never swallows them as embedded gitlinks)
06_survey_data_fetcher/
count_down/cd2030/
disruption_mapping/

# --- Personal runner / scratch scripts at repo root ---
/run_*.R
/test_*.R
/fetch_*.R
/plot_*.R
/Dockerfile
/run_in_docker.sh

# --- Personal Shiny viewers inside module folders (local-only) ---
m007/shiny_scorecard.R
